04:20.028 --> 04:22.295
Tiehteti.

04:22.330 --> 04:24.830
Eli. My name's Eli.

04:28.670 --> 04:31.604
You speak English?

04:32.707 --> 04:36.242
I'm Maggie Phelps.

04:36.277 --> 04:38.678
Stand up.

04:47.956 --> 04:49.021
How's it feel?

04:49.057 --> 04:50.489
Better.

04:50.525 --> 04:51.991
Swelling went down.

04:52.026 --> 04:54.594
We need to keep rubbing
that coneflower on you,

04:54.629 --> 04:56.796
mornings and night.

05:04.572 --> 05:07.240
Those savages know about coneflower?

05:10.511 --> 05:11.811
They call it tuka natsu.

05:11.846 --> 05:15.781
Well, look at you,
speaking their tongue.

05:15.817 --> 05:19.018
Well, you can forget
all that nonsense now.

05:19.053 --> 05:20.820
You made it out.

05:20.855 --> 05:23.723
Those Lamanites won't
lay another finger on you.

05:23.758 --> 05:27.226
They're Comanches.

05:27.270 --> 05:29.570
We call 'em Lamanites.

05:29.597 --> 05:31.030
Who's we?

05:31.065 --> 05:33.399
Settlers.

05:33.434 --> 05:36.035
Where's the rest of you?

05:36.070 --> 05:40.539
I had to go out on my own for a bit.

05:40.575 --> 05:42.375
But I will catch up with my people

05:42.410 --> 05:44.777
when providence deems it so.

05:48.516 --> 05:54.920
You ain't ever seen a wagon
train long as this, Eli...

05:54.956 --> 06:00.660
hundreds of us, fulfilling
a divine prophecy.

06:00.695 --> 06:01.994
Then why'd you leave?

06:02.030 --> 06:04.830
We parted ways in the
Indian territories.

06:04.866 --> 06:06.732
There was a disagreement with the elders

06:06.768 --> 06:11.203
necessitated me moving on.

06:11.239 --> 06:15.041
God knows my specialness...

06:15.076 --> 06:18.377
even if some of His
lesser creatures do not.

06:21.416 --> 06:24.116
So, it's just you out here all alone?

06:24.152 --> 06:25.584
It's just me.

06:25.620 --> 06:27.953
No family? No husband?

06:34.162 --> 06:37.096
My man, Liam, died.

06:37.131 --> 06:38.531
Felled not by savages,

06:38.566 --> 06:43.736
but a pain in his gut
from the bad water.

06:43.771 --> 06:45.971
I'm real sorry about that.

06:53.581 --> 06:55.548
You've lost family, too.

06:55.583 --> 06:59.251
I can tell.

06:59.287 --> 07:02.421
Any of 'em left?

07:02.457 --> 07:05.958
Just my daddy.

07:05.993 --> 07:08.661
Well...

07:08.696 --> 07:11.497
I can help you find him.

07:14.635 --> 07:19.472
Ft. Bent is just a few days ride.

07:19.507 --> 07:23.876
They're real good at reuniting
captives with their kin.

07:26.381 --> 07:28.447
I don't ever wanna see him again.

07:28.483 --> 07:30.249
Don't talk like that.

07:30.284 --> 07:31.417
Why not?

07:31.452 --> 07:32.585
He's your father.

07:32.620 --> 07:36.255
He got drunk, hit us all the time,

07:36.290 --> 07:38.257
made my Momma cry on
the account'a that whore

07:38.292 --> 07:41.093
he kept in San Antonio.

07:41.129 --> 07:43.028
I ain't got no loyalty for that man.

07:43.064 --> 07:46.599
And I sure the hell
ain't gonna live with him.

07:46.634 --> 07:48.467
Maggie, I appreciate your kindness,

07:48.503 --> 07:50.369
but I got to be somewhere.

07:50.405 --> 07:54.306
I'll be happy to do chores or hunt

07:54.342 --> 07:56.108
if you'd let me borrow a few things.

07:56.144 --> 08:00.312
What you need is rest.

08:00.348 --> 08:01.680
You don't understand.

08:01.716 --> 08:03.236
My people are gonna be looking for me.

08:03.251 --> 08:04.350
I need to get back to 'em.

08:04.385 --> 08:07.019
What people? The Lamanites?

08:17.432 --> 08:20.166
Those ain't people.

