09:12.429 --> 09:13.862
What?

09:13.897 --> 09:17.432
Hmm?

09:17.467 --> 09:19.367
What's going on in there?

09:19.410 --> 09:23.478
Just feeling... I dunno... happy?

09:28.111 --> 09:30.245
Well, you say that like a question.

09:30.280 --> 09:31.613
It's probably 'cause it's been a while

09:31.615 --> 09:33.748
since I felt that way.

09:33.784 --> 09:36.551
When I'm around you, it's
like nothing else matters.

09:36.587 --> 09:39.387
I don't feel ashamed.
I don't feel guilty.

09:39.423 --> 09:41.756
What do you have to be ashamed of?

09:41.792 --> 09:43.491
How much time you got?

09:46.430 --> 09:47.495
Us?

09:47.531 --> 09:49.335
No, not us.

10:13.390 --> 10:14.689
I've hurt a lot of people.

10:14.725 --> 10:18.293
You know that, right?

10:18.328 --> 10:20.662
You mean Sally?

10:20.697 --> 10:23.965
No. No.

10:24.001 --> 10:28.603
Well, yeah, but not just her.

10:28.639 --> 10:31.206
I've hurt a lot of people, Maria.

10:33.510 --> 10:36.511
Pete?

10:36.546 --> 10:38.380
My father gets home from Austin soon.

10:38.415 --> 10:40.682
We should probably go.

10:40.716 --> 10:44.018
Yeah, I should go, too.

10:44.054 --> 10:47.889
My family will be wondering where I am.

11:39.376 --> 11:41.609
Everything all right?

11:44.815 --> 11:46.915
I know who shot me.

11:50.954 --> 11:53.555
The daughter of that Apache kid.

11:55.592 --> 11:57.092
What Apache kid?

11:57.127 --> 12:00.628
The one I left on the riverbank.

12:00.664 --> 12:02.063
He was real?

12:02.099 --> 12:04.132
'Course he was.

12:04.167 --> 12:06.701
I always thought you invented
that part of the story.

12:06.737 --> 12:09.471
No. He was flesh, all right,

12:09.506 --> 12:11.139
and he grew up telling his daughter

12:11.174 --> 12:14.976
all about how I killed their people.

12:15.011 --> 12:18.580
She let me know right before
she pulled the trigger.

12:18.615 --> 12:20.115
Should we go after her?

12:20.150 --> 12:22.951
No. I'm grateful...

12:22.986 --> 12:27.288
grateful for her
showing up when she did.

12:27.324 --> 12:29.248
It was a sign.

12:30.761 --> 12:32.427
I'm being warned.

12:32.462 --> 12:34.462
What do you mean, it was a sign?

12:34.498 --> 12:35.997
Like magic?

12:36.032 --> 12:37.832
Well, call it what you want.

12:37.868 --> 12:40.602
I can't ignore it.

12:40.637 --> 12:44.239
I'm calling this off.

12:44.274 --> 12:46.508
Oh, no.

12:46.543 --> 12:48.243
You're not getting cold feet now.

12:48.278 --> 12:50.845
We just bribed a judge with
every last dollar we have.

12:50.881 --> 12:52.013
So get it back.

12:52.048 --> 12:53.168
Bribes don't work like that.

12:53.183 --> 12:54.916
I don't care!

12:54.951 --> 12:57.318
I've got principles.

12:57.354 --> 13:00.421
I never hurt anyone that
didn't come at me first.

13:00.457 --> 13:02.023
Pedro García... He's our friend.

13:02.058 --> 13:03.424
He saved our lives.

13:03.460 --> 13:06.027
If I attacked him,
what does that make me?

13:06.062 --> 13:07.529
This isn't easy, Daddy.

13:07.564 --> 13:09.297
No one's saying it is.

13:09.332 --> 13:11.866
You don't have children.

13:11.902 --> 13:16.871
You don't have to consider
what you're teaching them.

13:16.914 --> 13:19.347
Oh, you taught me and Pete
plenty back in the day,

13:19.376 --> 13:21.442
lessons I am not proud to have learned.

13:21.478 --> 13:24.612
I taught you to protect what's yours.

13:24.648 --> 13:26.867
This will be something different.

13:26.898 --> 13:28.394
Don't you understand?

13:28.405 --> 13:29.838
No. I don't understand at all.

13:29.858 --> 13:31.404
You sure this ain't
a man getting spooked

13:31.406 --> 13:32.453
'cause he just got shot?

13:32.489 --> 13:38.660
I've been shot or cut more
times than I can count.

13:38.695 --> 13:42.630
I'm spooked about something
that's a lot bigger.

13:42.666 --> 13:44.499
We're calling this off.

13:44.534 --> 13:46.801
You know we'll lose the ranch.

13:46.837 --> 13:48.505
Then we lose it.

13:57.912 --> 14:02.148
♪ Joy has no sorrow ♪

14:02.184 --> 14:06.119
♪ That heaven cannot heal ♪

14:06.154 --> 14:09.456
♪ The desolate ♪

14:12.894 --> 14:19.532
♪ Desolate, light of the straying ♪

14:19.568 --> 14:25.305
♪ Hope of light of the straying ♪

14:25.340 --> 14:29.375
♪ Hope of the glory ♪

14:29.411 --> 14:32.712
♪ Comforter ♪

14:32.747 --> 14:40.286
♪ And here comes the Comforter ♪

14:40.322 --> 14:43.931
♪ In God's name saying ♪

14:54.436 --> 14:55.502
You hungry?

14:55.537 --> 14:56.903
No.

14:56.938 --> 14:59.005
What's that?

14:59.040 --> 15:02.242
It's an instrument of revelation.

15:02.277 --> 15:04.177
Looks like rocks in a hat to me.

15:04.212 --> 15:07.380
I use it to divine prophecy.

15:07.415 --> 15:09.349
I don't believe that.

15:11.686 --> 15:16.556
Would you like to know your future?

15:16.591 --> 15:18.324
All right.

15:26.768 --> 15:31.171
Heavenly Lord, I humbly pray
for your wisdom and discernment.

15:31.206 --> 15:35.175
Illuminate me so that I can
testify to this young man

15:35.210 --> 15:38.811
his direction if it be your will.

15:57.499 --> 16:00.066
Well?

16:00.101 --> 16:02.602
You're gonna be a great warrior.

16:02.637 --> 16:05.438
Folks everywhere will know your name.

16:05.473 --> 16:08.041
Yeah?

16:08.076 --> 16:11.411
You will live a long life, Eli,

16:11.446 --> 16:16.249
and you will prosper beyond your dreams.

16:16.284 --> 16:18.284
What about Prairie Flower?

16:18.320 --> 16:19.842
- Who?
- My girl.

16:19.874 --> 16:21.321
We gonna get married?

16:21.356 --> 16:22.822
You will.

16:22.857 --> 16:25.758
And when you're a little older,

16:25.794 --> 16:29.429
you're gonna have three sons,

16:29.464 --> 16:33.933
strong and handsome.

16:33.969 --> 16:38.938
And the youngest will be your favorite.

16:59.494 --> 17:01.628
Hiya.

17:01.663 --> 17:03.696
Pete: How's it going, big brother?

17:03.732 --> 17:05.198
You all right?

17:05.233 --> 17:06.665
How's Daddy?

17:06.701 --> 17:08.835
Spent two weeks arguing
with the doctors,

17:08.869 --> 17:11.271
thinking he knows more than they do.

17:11.306 --> 17:13.873
Took everything in my power
to keep him from driving.

17:13.907 --> 17:16.342
Guess that's a victory.

17:16.377 --> 17:18.278
How'd his stitches take the trip?

17:18.313 --> 17:21.848
Fine... though we
can't get him worked up.

17:21.883 --> 17:24.117
Otherwise, his lung
might collapse again.

17:24.152 --> 17:26.352
Oh, man.

17:32.427 --> 17:34.093
Sorry about the state of things.

17:34.095 --> 17:35.461
Since the vaqueros quit,

17:35.497 --> 17:37.397
I've been doing the repairs by myself.

17:37.432 --> 17:39.132
Oh, I can see that.

17:39.167 --> 17:40.700
It's looking good.

17:42.337 --> 17:44.137
How you been otherwise?

17:44.172 --> 17:45.538
I'm fine.

17:45.573 --> 17:47.407
You don't pick up the phone when I call.

17:47.442 --> 17:48.508
Been worried.

17:48.543 --> 17:49.876
I got a lot on my plate.

17:49.911 --> 17:52.211
Mm, makes sense, you and Sally havin'

17:52.247 --> 17:54.547
this rough patch, after
all you been through.

17:54.582 --> 17:56.516
It's more than a rough patch.

17:56.551 --> 18:00.086
That true?

18:00.136 --> 18:02.103
I don't think we can
talk about this, Finn.

18:02.123 --> 18:04.724
I know you and Sally are close.

18:04.759 --> 18:07.026
You're my brother first.

18:10.535 --> 18:12.101
I hope you don't give up, is all.

18:12.136 --> 18:13.836
That's not your decision, Finn.

18:13.871 --> 18:16.038
What are you saying? Divorce?

18:16.074 --> 18:17.340
Eli: Is that Pete I hear?

18:17.375 --> 18:18.641
You're supposed to be resting.

18:18.676 --> 18:19.842
Bullshit.

18:19.877 --> 18:22.178
Let's get drunk.

18:24.582 --> 18:28.184
It was just before
I bought this ranch...

18:28.219 --> 18:30.386
the last days of the Civil War.

18:32.423 --> 18:35.725
I spent weeks trying to get
back to your mother in Austin.

18:35.760 --> 18:38.728
One night, I was camped
out by this stream,

18:38.763 --> 18:40.896
just sitting there, thinking.

18:40.932 --> 18:46.202
It was real quiet... hardly any wind.

18:46.237 --> 18:51.040
Then... out of nowhere...

18:51.876 --> 18:53.676
Aaaaah!

18:55.713 --> 18:57.980
It was a mountain lion.

18:58.016 --> 19:01.651
The bastard snuck up
about 10 feet behind me.

19:01.686 --> 19:05.921
And in that moment, I knew...

19:05.957 --> 19:08.424
"So, this is how I die.

19:08.459 --> 19:12.728
After the Comanches, the Tonks,
the Rangers, the Union Army,

19:12.764 --> 19:14.397
the thugs, the bandits,

19:14.432 --> 19:17.433
a goddamn lion will be my end!"

19:19.804 --> 19:22.171
How'd you get away?

19:22.206 --> 19:25.107
I didn't.

19:26.210 --> 19:28.878
The lion spared me.

19:31.816 --> 19:34.483
He just looked at me and walked off.

19:37.722 --> 19:39.822
It was a sign.

19:41.626 --> 19:44.794
It took everything I
had to buy this property.

19:44.829 --> 19:46.395
A lot of folks thought I was crazy,

19:46.431 --> 19:49.298
including your mother,
but I saw something in it

19:49.333 --> 19:54.704
that I loved, that I
wanted to build on...

19:54.739 --> 19:58.307
I was gonna give to you boys one day.

19:58.342 --> 20:00.976
I'm sorry that's not gonna happen now.

20:05.183 --> 20:09.485
What're you sayin', Daddy?

20:09.520 --> 20:10.920
Well, didn't your brother tell you?

20:10.955 --> 20:13.889
We're gonna sell this ol' place...

20:13.925 --> 20:16.325
just as soon as you fix it back up.

20:16.360 --> 20:18.027
Oh.

20:19.697 --> 20:21.931
We've lived a good life here.

20:21.966 --> 20:25.735
Yeah. Yeah, I guess we have.

20:27.371 --> 20:31.006
Yeah, I think it's better this way.

20:31.042 --> 20:34.443
You'll go back up to
Austin with the family,

20:34.479 --> 20:36.946
finally give Sally what she wants.

20:36.981 --> 20:38.647
That does make a lot of sense.

20:38.683 --> 20:40.716
Top you off?

20:44.155 --> 20:47.022
This could be good for all of
us, new beginnings and all that.

20:47.058 --> 20:50.793
I think I'm gonna get a
small patch up in North Texas,

20:50.828 --> 20:52.962
maybe about 20 head,

20:52.997 --> 20:55.030
somewhere where there's
a little bit more water.

20:55.066 --> 20:56.832
Probably gonna need a few hundred acres.

20:56.868 --> 20:59.869
No, probably not.

20:59.904 --> 21:02.605
Living wild, just
like the good old days.

